  "finger_focus": "Mostly right pinky, some Shift combos",
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "The last set, and a useful one: the operators. The plus joins, the angle brackets compare, the pipe offers a choice, the tilde marks an approximation. These five turn numbers into logic - the working language of math and code."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "The plus is Shift plus the equals key, right pinky. The angle brackets ride the comma and period: < is Shift+comma, > is Shift+period. The pipe is Shift plus the backslash, right pinky. The tilde sits top left, above Tab: ~ is Shift plus that key, left pinky."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "keyboard",
      "title": "Read the pairs",
      "text": "These rarely travel alone. == tests equal, != tests not-equal, <= and >= compare and include. Learn them as pairs, the way you read them, and they will come off the hand as one motion."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "+ + + < < < > > > + < > + < >",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Plus and angles",
      "hint": "+ is Shift+equals, < is Shift+comma, > is Shift+period."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "| | | ~ ~ ~ | ~ | ~ | ~ | ~",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Pipe and tilde",
      "hint": "| is Shift+backslash (right pinky), ~ is Shift+the top-left key (left pinky)."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "y < 10. z > 0. a == b. true | false. x += 1.",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Operators at work",
      "hint": "Compare with the angles, choose with the pipe, add with plus."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Here is the whole operator set in use: compare two values, offer a choice, mark an approximate, add one and move on. Master these and you have the symbols that carry most of a line of code. Accuracy is respect - for the word, the reader, and yourself."
    }
  ],
